ollectionWithIndex&x=CollectionWithIndex%3CE%3E&x=WithSize&x=ImageContent&x=Image&x=DataGrid&x=DataGrid.LoadSpec&x=Array%3Cmixing%20Store%3E&x=Collection%3Cmixing%20Store%3E&x=CollectionWithIndex%3Cmixing%20Store%3E&x=Int16Type:718:12)\n    at Proxy.f (eval at _bootstrap (eval at #buildConn (/home/coder/.local/share/code-server/extensions/c3ai.c3-ai-dx-v8-4.2.4/extension/out/node_modules/@c3/remote/index.js:91:18)), <anonymous>:9429:12)\n    at Proxy.fromAny (http://stgawstrn1-srinat-c3-k8ssvc-appleader-001:8888/srinat/academyfundamentals/typesys/8/DataGrid.js-client-node.js?tier=FULL&bootstrapped&x=ImplLanguage&x=ImplLanguage.Session&x=Identified&x=Identifiable&x=Js.TurboJsSession&x=DslComment&x=DeclaredReferenceType&x=ReferenceType&x=ValueType&x=DeclaredFieldType&x=InheritedValueType&x=MethodType&x=FunctionType&x=DateTimeType&x=PrimitiveType&x=StringType&x=NativeType&x=Action.Requirement&x=ImplLanguage.Session.SetupSpec&x=FieldType&x=FieldTypeAndMethodBase&x=Str&x=Annotations&x=Ann&x=Val&x=BooleanType&x=FunctionParam&x=VarReferenceType&x=LambdaType&x=Pkg&x=AppMode&x=Enum&x=Enum%3Cstring%3E&x=ArrayType&x=CollectionType&x=Boxed&x=Boxed%3C%3Fstring%3E&x=Ann.Ser&x=Annotation&x=MapType&x=AnyType&x=ImplLanguage.Session.ExecuteResult&x=IntType&x=NumberType&x=Content&x=ContentMeta&x=ContentTypeInfo&x=ContentValue&x=ReadOnlyContent&x=Base64&x=Boxed%3Cstring%3E&x=Notebook&x=JsonType&x=Notebook.Output&x=Notebook.Output.Kind&x=Pair&x=ByteStream&x=Closable&x=BinaryType&x=ByteType&x=StreamType&x=ContentEncoding&x=ContentType&x=Charset&x=CharStream&x=ImplLanguage.Session.HeartbeatResult&x=FetchResult&x=FetchResult%3Cmixing%20Store%3E&x=DataGriddable&x=Refreshable&x=Store&x=Persistable&x=Meta&x=DateTime&x=DoubleType&x=Int32Type&x=City&x=FetchSpec&x=FloatType&x=Array&x=Collection&x=Collection%3CE%3E&x=CollectionWithIndex&x=CollectionWithIndex%3CE%3E&x=WithSize&x=ImageContent&x=Image:94:22)"}}]}],"executionSummary":{"timing":{"startTime":1779398011448,"endTime":1779398011638},"executionOrder":27,"success":false}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"**Expected output**\n\nFor `store_001`, you should see the Sale records `sale_001` and `sale_002`.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"## Section 3: Data model traversal","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"When you set up connections between your Persistable Types using collection and reference fields, you can then traverse your data model using dot notation. Dot notation syntax allows you to navigate Types in a readable and expressive way. This can be helpful when you access fields within referenced objects. \n\nFor example, retrieve the age of a `Fixture` that a `SmartBulb` is in, we can use the dot notation expression `fixture.age` in a fetch query. The following graphic illustrates accessing the fields from the `SmartBulb` to the `Fixture` Type:\n\n<img src=\"../src/doc/img/lab2/fixture-age.png\" alt=\"Illustration of the expression Fixture.age and the accessing the corresponding fields on the SmartBulb and Fixture Types.\" width=\"500px\" style=\"padding: inherit;\n  margin:auto; display:block;\"/> \n\nYou encounter dot notation in any C3 AI application and many areas of the platform, like in data integration pipelines or data retrieval methods, in field definitions on persistable Types, time series data manipulation, and more. One place you will frequently encounter dot notation is in fetch calls.\n\nThe checkpoint in Activity 1.1 contains an example of dot notation usage. Let's examine how dot notation helps us access referenced objects in a data model using various fetch calls. We will start by inspecting the `LineItem` records returned from the fetch. ","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"javascript","value":"// Remember that `LineItem.product` is a reference field that points to the `Product` Type. \nLineItem.fetch()","output":[{"items":[{"mime":"c3/notebook","value":["{","\