nField: [SomeOtherType](fkey)\n\n}\n```\n\nYou also learned how to traverse a data model using dot notation. Dot notation makes traversing through a data model convenient.  Instead of joining multiple tables together, you simply write an expression in a string and retrieve the corresponding objects or data. \n\nAs you gain more experience with the C3 AI Type System, you are likely to encounter dot notation in a variety of contexts outside of the fetch examples shown in this lab.\n\nReturn to the course on learn.c3.ai to continue learning the C3 AI developer fundamentals.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"-----","output":[],"executionSummary":{}}],"metadata":{"id":"f4d0aec0-ee51-49a9-b05a-9ddc8ec810c3","appName":"academyfundamentals","serializerVersion":"1","runtime":"js-rhino"}}